13/06/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Authorities detained an alleged member of an Islamist group, prior to US President George W. 
Bush's weekend visit to Sofia, Interior Minister Rumen Petkov announced at a news conference Tuesday (June 12th). 
He said police received information the man had completed sharpshooter courses. 
Four other people were detained for allegedly making anonymous threats related to Bush's visit.
In other news Tuesday, Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov said the US military bases in Bulgaria would be ready next year, after the two sides seal agreements for their joint use later this year. 
(Sega - 13/06/07; Darik, Mediapool, BNR, Fena, AFP - 12/06/07)
